title: Waterford Hills Wednesday Night Race Series
2014 Zehnder's das Tour de Frankenmuth
description: Michigan's Largest One Day event for 3 years running.  Great course, great terrain, great cycling atmosphere.  Plan to stay for the balloon and dog bowl events in Frankenmuth. Make it a holiday weekend!
course: Course is new, safer, longer, 20 mile loop through the flat fields of Frankenmuth, MI.  Start and staging will be in front of Zehnder's Restaurant. Finish line is now on Gunzenhausen road at Rosstal.
registration: Packet pick up -Friday night will be at Zehnders Splash Village from 6:00 – 9:00 pm. Packet pick up begins Sat morning at 6;30 a.m. at start/finish area. No race day registration. You can register on line until Friday May 23rd, at 5pm. Registration increase by $5.00 after May 16.  $5 registration discount for beginner categories
notes:
Lodging: Zehnders Splash Village will be providing discounted room rates to racers wishing to stay on Friday night. This discounted rate is available before May 10. Call the hotel directly for availability at 1-800-863-7999. Or, book on line at http://www.zehnders.com/, be sure to mention the race for your discount.

Final Notes:
All riders, must show a valid license, One day licenses should be purchased before event through USACycling.org.
Helmets are required for all participants
USA Cycling rules apply.
All participants must sign USAC waiver
Riders under 18 years are required to have a parent or guardian’s signature on waiver
Payouts will be announced at the start of the race.
Minimum field participants of 10 riders required in each field to guarantee full prize listed. Directors reserve the right to combine fields or reduce awards based on participation. Contact race directors for information.
Boys and Girls under 19 do have the option of riding in the beginner category-which would require two laps.

MBRA Note: All combined Categories that race together  will be separated for challenge point’s series calculations.
directions: Parking will be in the rear of Zehnder's Restaurant, 730 S. Main St. Frankenmuth, MI  48734

Michigan Technological University Collegiate Mountain Race
description: The 2014 Michigan Tech Collegiate MTB races will be held in Houghton and Copper Harbor, MI. There will be cross country, short track, downhill, and dual slalom events. An optional, just-for-fun pump track competition will be ongoing Saturday.
course:
Short Track: Held on Michigan Tech ski and singletrack trails.
Dual Slalom: Held on Michigan Tech dual slalom course.
Cross Country: Approx. 9 mile loop at Copper Harbor trails, utilizing both technical old-school trails and new, machine built 'flow' trails.
Downhill: Held on Downtown trail in Copper Harbor. Full face helmet required.
registration: Early registration $15 per event. Price increase to $20 on Monday, Sept. 29 (week of event).
directions:
Michigan Tech: MTU trail head- South of campus on Sharon Avenue. 47°06'34.3"N 88°33'08.7"W
Copper Harbor: Copper Harbor trail head- intersection of Gratiot St. and Manganese Rd. Team van/bus parking available in parking lot at the corner of Gratiot and Second. 47°28'04.2"N 87°53'17.3"W
